4:
Hehe! I asked Santa for a Guild
Knight sword!
6:
You mean, the toy version, right?
You boys aren't cool enough to use
the real thing!
9:
Happy holidays! I've brought
presents for all the good boys and
girls!
13:
Here you go! It's an elemental gem.
You're all kids, so I got you the
smallest ones.
16: Huh? Who are you calling "kid," kid?
18:
Look at how pretty it is, though! It's
so sparkly... Thank you! Can I really
have this?
21:
You bet! It's Santa's job to give out
presents, after all!
26:
Elena, get away from that girl!
Children, come here this instant!
33: Tch... Now I'm in a bad mood.
37:
It seems adventurers aren't the only
ones frightened by Arum's
appearance... The townsfolk fear her
powers as well.
39:
That doesn't excuse their behavior,
of course...
45:
Here you go! I've got a present for
you too!
51:
Why not? You don't need to hold
back, you know. It's the holidays!
55:
I-I do just fine all by myself! I don't
need your pity!
61:
Besides, you shouldn't be giving out
presents that aren't even yours!
63:
Huh? But these ARE mine. I got them
all by myself.
66:
Liar! I have to scavenge for
elemental gem shards just to afford
food...
68:
There's no way a brat like you could
go into the Kaleidoscope. You're just
a big, fat LIAR!
80:
Yes... She seems to be an orphan.
And one living on the streets at that.
We will have to bring her to Lilie and—
85:
Fine! I'll show you that I can get
elemental gems all by myself!
88:
Lightsy, Nimbus! We're going to the
Kaleidoscope, and we're taking this
kid with us!
91:
Hey! I have a name, you know! Call
me Voula!
103:
Heh, well, now we can take care of
the brats and get some fighting in.
Two birds with one stone.
113:
Ugh... Fine... I guess you were telling
the truth...
117:
Is that all? I think there's something
else you should say to me.
123:
Hehe, it's okay! I'll be the bigger
person and forgive you!
127: All right, now it's your turn, Voula!
130:
Go on, give it a try! Make them go
boom!
133:
I-I can't do that, you idiot! I can't
even use magic!
136:
Whoa there, Arum... Doncha think
you're going a little overboard?
140:
Why? She can use magic. I feel it
inside her.
145:
I suppose we're safe on this floor...
Would you like to try?
148:
Arum's powers are quite special. Her
magic is also slightly different from
the magic I know. She could be
telling the truth...
153: So, uh... How long is this gonna take?
156:
Ah, no, Voula! You don't burn them!
You gotta MAKE them burn!
159:
I already told you that doesn't make
any sense!
164:
Okay, then I'll do it with you. Here,
take my hand.
167: I'll just pretend, okay? Just do as I do.
170:
See? I'm not burning them. I'm
MAKING them burn.
177: I... I did it! I beat that monster!
181: See? I told you so! Ahahaha!
188:
Now, we may not have run into
trouble today, but remember that
you are not to go into the
Kaleidoscope alone. Always take
one of us with you.
195:
*sigh* We fought all those monsters,
but we only got a few gems. That's
so dumb!
198:
I-it is not! I got these all by myself...
Hehe!
201:
Huh? But these are so tiny! The one I
was gonna give you is WAY bigger!
205:
Haha, earning something yourself
and getting it from someone else
are two completely different feelings.
211: H-hey, Arum. Um... Thanks for today...
214:
Why are you thanking me? You're
the one who beat those monsters.
217:
B-but you're the one who taught me
magic... So...
225:
Hehe, my tummy feels all warm and
fuzzy! That's so weird! Ahahaha!
